                <head>No. 690.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Admiral <persName type="from">Polo de Bernabé</persName> to
                        Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain at Washington</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-11-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 12, 1873</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The undersigned, minister plenipotentiary of Spain, has the honor to inform the
                    honorable Secretary of State, in reply to his note, that h$ has received no
                    advices, either official or unofficial, of the executions by shooting referred
                    to in the honorable Secretary’s dispatch of this date, which he has just
                    received now—that is to say, at 5 o’clock in the afternoon</p>
                <p>The undersigned, in hastening to reply to the aforesaid note of the honorable
                    Secretary of State, avails himself of this occasion to renew to him the
                    assurances of his most distinguished consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOSÉ POLO DE BERNABÉ</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
